An official letter from Caijing magazine.
《财经》杂志由中国证券市场研究中心主办，1998年创刊，秉承“独立、独家、独到”的新闻理念，以权威性、公正性、专业性报道见长，是政经学界决策者、研究者、管理者的必读刊物。
"Caijing" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was founded in 1998, upholding the news concept of "independence, exclusivity and originality," and providing authoritative, impartial and professional reports.
。
.
_新冠病毒肺炎疫情可能会导致中国经济活动受扰，但目前可能不会成为影响全球市场的主要因素。
The outbreak of _ new crown pneumonia could disrupt economic activity in China, but it is unlikely to be a major factor affecting global markets at the moment.
中美金融市场最近的表现，表明投资者担忧的疫情对金融市场的影响在减弱，从政府到个人的资金支持及捐赠，也提振了市场和人心_文 |《财经》特派记者 金焱 发自华盛顿编辑 | 苏琦美联储在近日提交给美国国会的最新货币政策报告中表示，最近爆发的新冠肺炎疫情可能会导致中国经济活动受扰，并会殃及全球其他经济体。
The recent performance of Chinese and US financial markets suggests that investors' worries about the epidemic are weakening in financial markets. Financial support and donations from the government to individuals have also boosted the market and people's hearts and minds. The recent outbreak of New Crown Pneumonia could disrupt economic activity in China and hurt other economies around the world, Suqi said in a recent monetary policy report to Congress.
花旗集团前全球外汇主管、深数宏观（DeepMacro）联合创始人兼CEO杰弗瑞·杨（Jeffrey Young）则对《财经》记者表示，他们通过对网站实时追踪，通过大数据来判断疫情对经济的影响，目前来看可能不会成为主要因素。
Jeffrey Young, Citigroup's former global foreign-exchange director and co-founder and CEO of Deep Macro, told Caijing that by tracking the site in real time and using big data to gauge the impact of the epidemic on the economy, it is unlikely to be a major factor.
以维基百科访问量为例，人们对“冠状病毒”中文简体维基百科的访问量领先英文版本的访问量。
Taking Wikipedia traffic as an example, the number of visits to the coronavirus simplified Chinese Wikipedia is ahead of the English version.
英文版本的信息对全球市场的影响最大，因此可通过观察中文简体版的访问量来预测全球市场的风险状况。
The English version of the information has the greatest impact on the global market, so it is possible to predict the risk profile of the global market by looking at the number of visits in simplified Chinese.
杰弗瑞·杨告诉《财经》记者，目前，对“冠状病毒”中文简体的访问量较为稳定，表明新型冠状病毒可能目前不会成为影响全球市场的主要因素。
Jeffrey Young told Caijing that traffic to the coronavirus simplified Chinese is stable, suggesting that the new coronavirus may not be a major factor affecting the global market.
抗击疫情需要大量的医疗和人道主义物资。
The fight against the epidemic requires a great deal of medical and humanitarian supplies.
世卫组织近日发出了6.75亿美元的募捐呼吁。
WHO has recently launched a $675 million appeal.
世卫组织总干事谭德塞认为，6.75亿美元的战略准备和应对呼吁将支持各国通过更好的预防措施和更快的感染诊断来保护其人民。
According to the Director-General of WHO, Thence, the $675 million strategic preparedness and response appeal will support countries in protecting their populations through better prevention measures and faster infection diagnosis.
截至2月8日24时，根据中国有关机构公布的数据，中国境内现有确诊病例33738例(其中重症病例6188例)，累计治愈出院病例2649例(黑龙江核减1例)，累计死亡病例811例，累计报告确诊病例37198例(山西、黑龙江、河南、海南各核减1例)，现有疑似病例28942例。
As of 2400 hours on February 8, according to the data released by the Chinese authorities, there were 33,738 confirmed cases in China (including 6,188 severe cases), 2,649 cumulative cases of discharge (1 case of nuclear reduction in Heilongjiang), 811 cumulative cases of death and 37,198 cases of confirmed cases (one case each in Shanxi, Heilongjiang, Henan and Hainan).
累计追踪到密切接触者371905人，尚在医学观察的密切接触者188183人。
A cumulative total of 371,905 contacts were traced, with 18,8183 close contacts still under medical observation.
2月8日，美国驻北京大使馆发言人表示，被确诊为冠状病毒的60岁美国公民于2月6日在武汉市金银潭医院死亡。
On February 8, a spokesman for the U.S. Embassy in Beijing said that a 60-year-old American citizen diagnosed with coronavirus died on February 6 at the Gold and Silver Pool Hospital in Wuhan.
一名美国人成为新冠状病毒的首位确诊非华裔死亡者。
An American has become the first non-Chinese to be diagnosed with the new coronavirus.
日本外务省表示，一名在武汉因肺炎住院的日本男子，在出现与新冠状病毒相同的流感样症状后也死亡。
A Japanese man hospitalized with pneumonia in Wuhan died of the same flu-like symptoms as the new coronavirus, the foreign ministry said.
截止目前，新冠病毒疫情的致死人数已超过当年非典疫情的死亡人数。
So far, the death toll from the new crown virus epidemic has exceeded the number of deaths from the SARS epidemic that year.
在2002-2003年的非典（SARS）流行期间，记录的死亡人数是774人。
During the SARS epidemic of 2002-2003, 774 deaths were recorded.
美国总统特朗普2月7日称赞中国国家主席习近平对新冠病毒疫情做出了“迅速、有力和非常集中”的反应。
US President Trump praised Chinese President Xi Jinping on February 7 for his "rapid, forceful, and highly focused" response to the new crown virus.
中国央行副行长潘功胜近日在新闻发布会上说，此次疫情对中国经济的影响只是暂时的、阶段性的，不会改变中国经济长期向好、高质量增长的基本面。
'The impact of the epidemic on the Chinese economy is only temporary and gradual and will not change the fundamentals of China's long-term growth to good and high quality, 'Vice President Pan Gongsheng said at a recent news conference.
此前，中国央行累计向金融系统注入了人民币1.7万亿元的流动性。
The move comes after the People's Bank of China injected 1.7 trillion yuan of liquidity into the financial system.
在新冠病毒疫情的影响下，中美股市在中国春节前后都出现了较大幅度的下跌。
Under the influence of the new crown virus epidemic, the Chinese and American stock market both appeared before and after the Chinese New Year.
但刚刚过去的一周时间里，中美股市都扭转了跌势，中国创业板指数则是创出了年内新高，美国股市标普500指数也触及纪录高位。
But in the past week, both Chinese and American stocks have reversed course, with China's GEM index hitting a new year high and the US stock market's S & P 500 index hitting a record high.
投资机构分析人士认为，中美金融市场最近的表现表明，投资者所担忧的疫情对金融市场的影响在减弱，政府的支持和各方面的捐赠，也提振了市场和人心。
Analysts at investment houses say the recent performance of Chinese and US financial markets shows that investors' fears about the impact of the epidemic on financial markets are waning, and that government support and donations from various sources have boosted markets and sentiment.
有报道称，世卫组织已经从其紧急财政储备中拿出900万美元来帮助抗击疫情。
It is reported that WHO has allocated $9 million from its emergency financial reserves to help fight the epidemic.
此外，世卫组织向24个国家分发了约50万个口罩、35万副医用手套、4万套呼吸用品和约1万8000件隔离衣。
In addition, WHO distributed approximately 500,000 surgical masks, 350,000 medical gloves, 40,000 sets of respiratory supplies and approximately 18,000 pieces of protective clothing to 24 countries.
世卫组织总干事谭德塞2月7日指出， “在患者护理之外不恰当地广泛使用保护材料使短缺情况进一步恶化。
"Inadequate and widespread use of protective material outside patient care further exacerbates the shortage," WHO Director-General Theresa Tupper said on February 7.
结果，库存用尽了，积累的订单达到四到六个月。
As a result, inventories are depleted and orders accumulate to four to six months.
口罩和呼吸器的全球储备不足以满足世卫组织及其合作伙伴的需求。
Global stocks of respirators and respirators are insufficient to meet the needs of WHO and its partners.
”世卫组织表示，卫生工作者能够使用这些保护物品是当务之急。
The WHO says it is imperative that health workers be able to use these protective items.
其次是那些生病或照顾病人的人。
Then there are those who are ill or take care of the sick.
世卫组织建议不要在传播率低的国家和地区囤积保护材料。
WHO advises against stockpiling protective materials in countries and areas with low transmission rates.
当地时间2月8日，美国国务院发言人奥特葛斯在美国驻中国大使馆的微博上说：“本周，美国国务院协助向中国人民运送了近17.8吨的医疗和人道主义捐赠物资。
"This week, the U.S. State Department helped deliver nearly 17.8 tons of medical and humanitarian donations to the Chinese people," State Department spokesman Scott Otellis told a microblog at the US embassy in Beijing.
美国是世界上最慷慨的捐助方，今后将依然如此。
The United States is the world's most generous donor and will remain so.
我们鼓励世界其他各方向我们看齐，做出应有的承诺。
We encourage the rest of the world to follow our lead and make the commitment they deserve.
”稍早之前，美国驻华大使馆表示，美国国务院本星期协助完成了向中国人民捐赠近17.8公吨医疗物资的运送工作。
Earlier, the US embassy in Beijing said the US State Department helped complete the delivery of nearly 17.8 metric tons of medical supplies to the Chinese people this week.
这些物资包括口罩、防护衣、纱布、呼吸器等重要物品。
These include important items such as masks, protective clothing, gauze and respirators.
这些捐助物品体现了美国人民慷慨捐助的精神。
These donations reflect the generosity of the American people.
美国国务卿蓬佩奥2月7日宣布美国将提供最多达1亿美元的资金，帮助中国和其它国家抗击新型冠状病毒疫情。
US Secretary of State Pompeii announced on February 7 that the United States would provide up to $100 million to help China and other countries fight the new coronavirus outbreak.
美国政府之外，日本外务省已在1月底将一批支援物资转交中方。
In addition to the US government, Japan's Foreign Ministry handed over a batch of support materials to China at the end of January.
这批物资包括约1.5万个口罩、5万双手套、8000副防护镜、2000个医用口罩以及个人防护服50套。
The shipment consisted of approximately 15,000 face masks, 50,000 pairs of hand sets, 8,000 pairs of protective goggles, 2,000 medical masks and 50 sets of personal protective clothing.
同机抵达的还有东京都政府捐赠的约2万套防护服。
Some 20,000 protective suits donated by the Tokyo metropolitan government also arrived on board.
比尔及梅琳达·盖茨基金会(Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation) 2月5日宣布，将提供1亿美元资金用于抗击新型冠状病毒疫情。
The Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation announced February 5 that it would provide $100 million to fight the new coronavirus outbreak.
基金会的声明说，这笔资金可用于疾病监测、隔离和治疗工作，保护危险群体，还可用于疫苗以及诊疗方法的研发。
The foundation's statement says the money could be used for disease surveillance, isolation and treatment, for the protection of at-risk groups, and for the development of vaccines and diagnostic and therapeutic methods.
另有报道称，对冲基金公司Citadel创始人格瑞芬（Ken Griffin）也决定向中国捐赠750万，帮助新冠病毒重灾区湖北省抗击疫情。
It was also reported that Ken Griffin, founder of hedge fund Citadel, had decided to donate 7.5 million to China to help fight the outbreak in Hubei province, a region hit by the virus.
这笔捐赠中，斥资100万美元从欧洲购买的口罩、防护服、消毒液，目前已在送往武汉新华医院的途中。
The donation, which includes $1 million in masks, protective clothing and disinfectant from Europe, is on its way to Wuhan Xinhua Hospital.
遍布世界华人华侨也以各种方式开展爱心接力，捐款赠物，驰援中国战疫情。
The Chinese people all over the world also carry out a relay of love in various ways, donating gifts, to help China with the war epidemic.
据凤凰网报道，北京时间2月8日晚上，一架东航货机从美国洛杉矶抵达上海浦东机场,机上载有众多美国华侨和在美华人捐赠的防疫救灾物资共计12010箱,总重46吨,其包含的28万套医用防护服和13万只口罩，将捐赠给武汉红十字会和江苏省昆山市政府,支援疫情防控第一线。
On the night of Feb. 8, a cargo plane from Los Angeles arrived at Shanghai's Pudong airport, carrying 12010 boxes of anti-epidemic supplies donated by overseas Chinese and Chinese in the US and weighing 46 tons, including 280,000 medical suits and 130,000 face masks.
